'''Auto''' is a subgenre of [[Drama|dramatic literature]]. It was a one-act [[morality play]], interlude or [[Sketch comedy|skit]].<ref>Kaler, Anne K. [https://books.google.com/books?id=s_IUCMcwFkMC&pg=PA24&dq=auto+play+%22gil+vincente%22#v=onepage&q=auto%20play%20%22gil%20vincente%22&f=false ''The picara: from Hera to fantasy heroine'']. Popular Press, 1991, page 24. {{ISBN|978-0879725167}}. Retrieved January 20, 2012</ref> They were first found in Spain, in the 15th century.<ref>Kurtz, Johann Heinrich. [https://books.google.com/books?id=2yo_AAAAYAAJ&pg=PA487&dq=auto+play+%22gil+vincente%22#v=onepage&q=auto%20play%20%22gil%20vincente%22&f=false ''Text-book of church history, Volumes 1–2'']. Smith, English & Co., 1880, page 487. Retrieved January 20, 2011.</ref> In [[Portugal]], in the 16th century, [[Gil Vicente]] was the main author of this type of dramatic genre. [[Luís de Camões]] and [[Dom Francisco Manuel de Mello]] also adopted this form of writing.

