'''Crimson Cow''' is a [[Germany|German]] [[video game publisher]] that was founded in 2002.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pc.gamespy.com/pc/a-vampyre-story/856250p1.html |title=GamersGate Open for German Publisher Crimson Cow |publisher=[[GameSpy]] |date=2008-03-03 |accessdate=2013-03-24}}</ref> They hold the German license for the [[Runaway: A Road Adventure|Runaway series]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2008/03/25/crimson-cow-releases-10-brand-new-screenshots-from-its-upcoming-adventure-the-abbey |title=Crimson Cow Releases 10 Brand New Screenshots From Its Upcoming Adventure, The Abbey |date=2008-03-25 |accessdate=2013-06-24 |publisher=[[IGN]]}}</ref> and the worldwide publishing rights for [[A Vampyre Story]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Publisher revealed for A Vampyre Story |url=http://www.adventuregamers.com/news/view/20090 |date=2006-07-07 |accessdate=2013-06-24 |publisher=[[Adventure Gamers]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://betax1.justadventure.com/Press_Releases/VampyreStoryCrimsonCow_Feb24_07.shtm |title=Crimson Cow expands its distribution network for A Vampyre Story |publisher=[[Just Adventure]] |date=2007-02-24 |accessdate=2013-07-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130628020413/http://betax1.justadventure.com/Press_Releases/VampyreStoryCrimsonCow_Feb24_07.shtm |archivedate=2013-06-28 |df= }}</ref>
