{{Infobox museum | name = The Museum of Oriental Ceramics, Osaka | native_name = 大阪市立東洋陶磁美術館 | native_name_lang = jpn | image = The Museum of Oriental Ceramics Osaka01bs2001.jpg | imagesize = 200 | caption = Exterior of the museum | alt = Exterior of the Museum of Oriental Ceramics, Osaka | map_type = Japan | map_size =200 | map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|34.693444|135.505472|type:landmark_region:JP|display=inline,title}} | established = {{Start date|1982|11|07}} | location = [[Osaka]], [[Japan]] | type = [[Art museum]] | collection = | visitors = | director = [[Degawa Tetsurō]] | president = | curator = | owner = | publictransit = | car_park = | network = | website = {{URL|moco.or.jp}} }}
The {{nihongo|'''Museum of Oriental Ceramics, Osaka'''|大阪市立東洋陶磁美術館|}} is a [[Japan]]ese [[art museum]] and regarded as one of the best ceramic-collections in the world. This museum collects, studies, conserves, exhibits and interprets East Asian ceramics, which mainly came from ancient [[China]] and [[Korea]]. The world-famous ''Ataka Collection'', donated by the 21 companies of the [[Sumitomo Group]], as well as the ''Rhee Byung-Chang Collection'', provide the public an aesthetic experience with first-class collection.<ref>[http://www.moco.or.jp/en/aboutus_01.html About Our Museum], MOC</ref>
== Collection == [[File:Spotted Celadon KONOIKE.JPG|thumb|Celadon vase with Iron Brown Spots]] === National Treasures === * Celadon vase with Iron Brown Spots * Tenmoku Glaze bowl with Silvery Spots
=== Important Cultural Properties === * Stoneware with Sgraffito Decoration of Peony with Transparent Glaze under Green Glaze * Porcelain with Carved Lotus Design * Porcelain with Incised Peony Scrolls Design Cut through Underglaze Iron-Coating * Celadon with Carved Peony Scrolls Design * Celadon vase with phoenix handles * Tenmoku Glaze bowl with Leaf Design * Blue-and-White with Fish and Water Plants Design * Blue-and-White with Peony Scrolls Design * Blue-and-White with Bird and Branch Design
